    stem: "A 28-year-old female at 37 weeks gestation presents with sudden onset of profuse, painless bright red vaginal bleeding. She has had no contractions. Fetal heart tones are normal. She had a low-lying placenta documented on her 20-week ultrasound. What should the emergency nurse avoid?",
