    stem: "A 34-year-old female presents 10 days postpartum with acute onset of shortness of breath, tachycardia, and leg swelling. She had a cesarean delivery and has been mostly bedridden since. D-dimer is elevated. CT pulmonary angiography confirms bilateral pulmonary emboli. What makes this patient high-risk for venous thromboembolism?",
